#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:7
msgid "Notes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:8
msgid ""
"All cut-off dates are based on 10am (San Francisco Time) on the day "
"stated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:9
msgid ""
"T-minus counts are measured in \"working days\" (weekdays, Monday through"
" Friday, excluding the listed statutory holidays) prior to release day."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:11
msgid "A. (T-minus 4 working days) Code Complete"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:13
#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:46
msgid "Release Manager:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:14
msgid ""
"Once the list of security issues to be fixed is finalized, post this "
"checklist in Release Checklist channel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:15
msgid ""
"Notify community about upcoming security release through a Twitter "
"announcement and in changelog with links to approved fixes and a date "
"tagged as \"TBD\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:16
msgid "Email GitLab release team about upcoming security release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:17
msgid ""
"Work with a developer to submit GitLab MR following this process and test"
" the upgrade once the GitLab MR is merged and included in their RC."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:18
msgid "Open a ticket to submit GitLab Omnibus RC install of Mattermost"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:19
msgid ""
"Make a post in Announcements channel announcing the security release to "
"the rest of the team with links to approved tickets and include a link to"
" the ticket to submit the GitLab MR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:20
#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:42
msgid "Dev:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:21
msgid "PRs for hotfixes are made to release branch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:22
msgid ""
"Review PRs made from release branch and merge changes into the release "
"branch as required and merge the release branch back into master once per"
" day"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:24
msgid "B. (T-minus 3 working days) Release Candidate Cut"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:26
msgid "Build:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:27
msgid ""
"Verify with Release Manager before cutting any new dot release RCs "
"(approved fixes should be merged)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:29
msgid "C. (T-minus 2 working days) Release Candidate Testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:31
msgid "QA:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:32
msgid ""
"If the dot release takes place during a regular release, update "
"prev.test.mattermost.com to dot-release RCs for the previous release and "
"keep rc.test.mattermost.com on the latest regular release version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:33
msgid "Test the new RC to verify fixes merged to the release branch work"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:34
msgid "Post in Release Discussion channel after testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:35
msgid "Logistics:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:36
msgid ""
"If the security researcher has not previously received a security "
"researcher mug, order one for them"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:38
msgid "D. (T-minus 0 working days) Release Build Cut"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:40
msgid "Once security fix release is ready to cut:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:43
msgid "Tag a new release (e.g., 1.1.1) and run an official build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:44
msgid "Verify hashes and GPG signatures are correct, once build is cut"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:45
msgid "Delete RCs after final version is shipped"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:47
msgid "Update the Changelog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:48
msgid "Update the version archive"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:49
msgid "Update the ESR documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:50
msgid ""
"Update Mattermost server download page with the links to the EE and TE "
"bits"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:51
msgid "Test the download links before and after updating the page"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:52
msgid ""
"Confirm that mattermost-docker has been updated to the latest version "
"(contact the maintainer via direct message on community server if "
"necessary)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:53
msgid ""
"Contact owners of community installers or submit PRs to update install "
"version number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:54
msgid ""
"For Puppet, Heroku and Ansible Playbook, post to Installers and Images "
"channel announcing the new release. See example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:55
msgid ""
"For Chef Cookbook, open a new issue to announce the new release. See "
"example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:56
msgid "For Yunohost, open a new pull request to update the version. See example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:57
msgid "For OpenShift, open a new pull request to update the version. See example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:58
msgid ""
"Update Security Research Hall of Fame on the Responsible Disclosure "
"Policy page"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:59
msgid "Post Mattermost Security Updates 30 days after the dot release has shipped"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:60
msgid ""
"Update Security Issues spreadsheet with issue number from posted update "
"(e.g. v3.2.0.1)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:61
msgid "Marketing:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security-release.md:62
msgid ""
"Prepare blog post for mattermost.com, MailChimp email blast, and Twitter "
"announcement, and send to marketing lead for review. Once reviewed, "
"schedule for 08:00 PST on the day after dot release"
msgstr ""

